The praetor’s interdict was a provisional order, issued generally in connexion with disputes about property, forbidding interference with or derangement of an existing posi· tion, and in some cases (as where force had already been employed) directing immediate restitution. This was the interdictum restitutorium, recuperandae possessionis causa, Gaius iv. 140-1.
